FBIS3-41585 "jpten004___94055" JPRS-TEN-94-004 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Environmental Issues 17 February 1994 EAST EUROPE POLAND Government To Seek Environmental Protection Convention LD1511141093 Warsaw PAP in English 1327 GMT 15 Nov 93 LD1511141093 Warsaw PAP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Warsaw, Nov 15 -- Minister of Environmental Protection, Natural Resources and Forestry Stanislaw Zelichowski on Monday announced that Poland will ask the Czech Republic, Slovakia, Ukraine and Belarus to sign a convention in which the four countries will state they will not implement investment projects which are unfriendly to the natural environment of their neighbours. Speaking at a press conference, the minister also said that ``ecology is without frontiers.'' ``The issues of the environmental protection are common in our part of Europe and therefore, establishing closer cooperation ties with our neighbours will be one of the ministry's policies,'' he added.
